cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper is about using BiLSTM models for PoS tagging, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses incorporating a morphological lexicon and a lexical category identification step, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses techniques such as data sparsity reduction and fine-grained tagsets, which are common in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper focuses on a specific language, Icelandic, which could make it relevant to the sub-category cs.CY (Computational Linguistics and Natural Language Processing).
